<p>Similar to the pair correlation function defined in Equation (1), the exponential decay of 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm60">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>G</mi>
      <mi>n</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">r</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> indicates short-range BO orientational order, while the algebraic decay of 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm61">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>G</mi>
      <mi>n</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">r</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, or its approaching to constant nonzero value at 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm62">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>r</mi>
     <mo>→</mo>
     <mo>∞</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> correspond to a quasi-long-range and long-range BO order, respectively.
</p>
